# Cursor Rules

## Language Requirements

All code, comments, documentation, variable names, function names, class names, commit messages, and communication must be in English.

### Code Standards

- All code comments must be written in English
- All variable names, function names, and class names must use English words
- All string literals and user-facing messages should be in English
- All error messages and log statements must be in English

### Documentation Standards

- All documentation files (README.md, \*.md) must be written in English
- All code documentation (docstrings, JSDoc comments, etc.) must be in English
- All API documentation must be in English

### Communication Standards

- All commit messages must be in English
- All code review comments should be in English
- All project-related communication should be in English

### Exceptions

- Only exception: file paths and URLs may contain non-English characters if necessary
- Configuration values that reference external systems may use their native language if required
